  "prompt": "What is the success ratio to get B1/B2 visa?",
  "response": "The success ratio for obtaining a B1/B2 visa (business and tourist visa) can vary based on several factors, including the applicant's country of origin, individual circumstances, and the specifics of their application. Typically, approval rates can fluctuate year by year and may be influenced by changing immigration policies, economic conditions, or other factors.\n\nAs of my last knowledge update in October 2023, it's worth noting that approval rates for B1/B2 visas can be higher for applicants from countries with strong ties to the United States, whereas applicants from countries with a history of higher visa refusal rates may experience lower success rates. Consular officers assess each application on a case-by-case basis, considering factors such as the applicant's financial situation, ties to their home country, purpose of travel, and overall credibility.\n\nFor the most accurate and current statistics, it's best to refer to the U.S. Department of State's Bureau of Consular Affairs or specific embassy websites, which periodically publish visa issuance statistics and trends.",
